340
00:25:24,481 --> 00:25:28,031
<i>Wallace started the second ballot
firmly in the lead...</i>

341
00:25:28,193 --> 00:25:30,321
<i>...but gradually he lost
ground to Truman...</i>

342
00:25:30,487 --> 00:25:35,584
<i>...as the nominees put up by Hannegan signed
over their votes to Truman, one by one.</i>

343
00:25:35,743 --> 00:25:39,293
<i>Truman prevailed. It was over.</i>

344
00:25:47,129 --> 00:25:51,179
I guess this is just another lost cause,
Mr. Paine.

345
00:25:54,887 --> 00:25:58,482
All you people don't know
about lost causes.

346
00:25:58,640 --> 00:26:00,734
Mr. Paine does.

347
00:26:02,478 --> 00:26:06,984
He said once they were the only causes
worth fighting for.

348
00:26:07,149 --> 00:26:12,827
And he fought for them once.
