349
00:26:12,988 --> 00:26:16,834
And you know that you fight for the
lost causes harder than for any others.

350
00:26:16,992 --> 00:26:21,168
Yes, you even die for them.
You think I'm licked.

351
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:28,422
You all think I'm licked.
Well, I'm not licked!

352
00:26:28,629 --> 00:26:31,849
And I'm gonna stay right here
and fight for this lost cause!

353
00:26:32,007 --> 00:26:35,887
Even if this room gets filled with lies
like these...

354
00:26:36,053 --> 00:26:41,526
...and the Taylors and all their armies
come marching into this place...

355
00:26:41,683 --> 00:26:44,903
...somebody will listen to me.

356
00:26:54,404 --> 00:26:57,032
<i>Henry Wallace, accepting his defeat..</i>

357
00:26:57,199 --> 00:27:00,419
<i>...pledged his loyalty
to the Roosevelt-Truman ticket...</i>

358
00:27:00,828 --> 00:27:03,877
<i>...and agreed to remain in the cabinet.</i>

359
00:27:04,039 --> 00:27:08,294
<i>Today, buried by the traditional tale
of the Second World War...</i>

360
00:27:08,460 --> 00:27:13,512
<i>...the events of the 1944 Democratic
Convention have been largely forgotten.</i>

361
00:27:13,674 --> 00:27:17,395
<i>They would however change
the course of history.</i>

362
00:27:17,553 --> 00:27:20,227
<i>The man who might have been president...</i>

363
00:27:20,389 --> 00:27:25,691
<i>...could now only watch from the sidelines
